Locations.14: North on I-95 to exit 19. Take a left at the end of the ramp onto center street. Go through a stop sign and make a left at the first set of traffic lights onto the post road. Locations.15: Merritt Parkway to Exit 38. Continue about 2 miles and turn right at light onto CT-106/Silvermine Road. Continue 1.4 miles to 4-way stop, and turn left onto Valley Road. Locations.14: From Westport and points South---take 95N and get off exit 19. Take a left at the bottom of the exit ramp. Go straight to the first light. This is the Post Road--make a left. Your first light is Hulls Highway (Vincent Decorators on the right). Make a right and follow to the stop sign. Make a left onto Hulls Farm Road. Take the first right onto Sturges Highway. Follow Sturges Highway for about 3 miles. DO NOT go left onto Cross Highway. Stay to the right and the road becomes Cross Highway. The Patterson Club will be on your left a mile further down the road. The courts are on your left.

Locations.15:
Take the Merritt Parkway North to Exit 42 (Westport/Weston).  At the bottom of the exit ramp, make a left at the light and then go straight thru the first stop sign.  (At this stop sign, 136 splits N and S with 136 S curving off to the right - do not curve, go straight toward 136 N). 
Continue straight up a slight hill for a short time past Daybreak Nursery until you come to the next stop sign and make a L onto Cross Highway. 
You will continue straight for quite a while on Cross Highway thru 2 stop signs (1 at North and 1 at Bayberry).  At the bottom of a steep hill, you will come to a stop sign and a dead end – make a L and continue on Cross Highway until you come to Patterson.  Parking lot is first on the L hand side, tennis courts on the R.

Locations.14: Take I-95 North to exit 10, turn left at the light onto Noroton Avenue. At the third light  take a left on to West Ave. at the Getty station. Go straight through the blinking light and at the first stop light, take a right on to Hollow Tree Ridge Rd.  At the second stop sign, the entrance to Wee Burn will be directly ahead. You can also get off exit 36 of the Merrit Parkway North and take a right onto Hoyt Street (Route 106). Make a left at the first light onto Talmadge Hill Road, cross the train tracks, and turn right at the stop sign onto Hollow Tree Ridge Rd. Follow it to the Wee Burn entrance, which will be on your left.
